dct_description_sm: Published by A. Finley Philada. ; Young & Delleker Sc.
Longitudinal and latitudinal lines (Greenwich and Washington meridians).
Provinces distinguished by coloring and dotted lines.
Shows waterways, boundaries, cities, "Imperial Canal," Great Wall, "Barrier of Wood," "Independent" provinces.
Likely taken from Finley's " A New General Atlas Comprising a Complete Set of Maps, representing the Grand Divisions Of The Globe."
"Formosa" uncolored, Korea colored. Unlike other editions "Tungquin" province (North Vietnam) colored in green and "Yunnan" in orange.
